# Problem

We have the following logic on the backend where we do not compute certain formula parts if GLcodes are not enabled. However, on the front end, we are not checking this key yet because previously it was  not returned with the policy.

```php
        if ($policy->areGlCodesEnabled()) {
            $employee = $policy->getEmployeeByEmail($email);
            if (!$employee) {
                return '';
            }
            if ($this->fieldEqualsTo(['userid', 'customfield1'], $fieldIndex)) {
                return $employee->getEmployeeUserID();
            }
            if ($this->fieldEqualsTo(['payrollid', 'customfield2'], $fieldIndex)) {
                return $employee->getEmployeePayrollID();
            }
        }

        return '';
```

# Solution
Now the data is present on the policy and we should check it to match the backend. This change is needed for proper optimistic report computation.

